<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 3.5: ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS,
        ACCELERATOR PEDAL POSITION SENSOR/IVS SWITCH (APS/IVS) - OWL (OIL WATER LAMP) / EWPS (ENGINE WARNING AND
        PROTECTION SYSTEM) - FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>An open or short to ground can be detected in the OWL circuit during an "On Demand" Engine Standard Test
            by the technician. A momentary bulb check can also be visually observed each time the ignition switch is
            turned on by the operator.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="BOLD">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1901796">3.80</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the owl engine warning and protection circuit diagram and
            <emph type="BOLD">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1901797">3.28</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the connector checks.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1901796" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg7318" filename="../figeg7/EG7318.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.80 Oil Water Lamp/Engine Warning And Protection System</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Before performing any diagnostic tests, check OWL Lamp and determine if burnt out.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <table id="t19017181">
            <title>Table 3.28 Oil Water Lamp/Engine Warning and Protection System Connector Checks</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="54p"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="54p"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="180p"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="S1T3"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Key On Engine Off - Voltage Checks</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">(Check with ECM chassis connector (black) unplugged, breakout box
                                    installed, Ign. key on, engine off)
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>+Test Points-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>F1 to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Fuse for instrument cluster and OWL lamp</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>B to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Battery voltage should be present from F1 to buzzer, if no voltage present, check
                                circuit for open or short.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>54 to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Battery voltage should be present from lamp circuit to ECM, if no voltage present,
                                check circuit for open or short.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Harness Resistance Check</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">(Check with ECM chassis connector (blk) unplugged, instrument cluster
                                    connector unplugged and Ign. key off)
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>54 to (10)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Continuity from ECM to cluster connector for OWL lamp</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>54 to C</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Continuity from ECM to Buzzer connector</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(10) to C</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Continuity from instrument cluster connector to Buzzer</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(5) to F1</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Continuity from instrument cluster connector to Fuse</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>B to F1</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Continuity from Buzzer to fuse</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Functional Checks</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Physical Circuit Check</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>Physical check - with breakout box installed momentarily ground ECM chassis pin # 54,
                                the OWL lamp should illuminate if the OWL circuit is good.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Output State Check</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>The OWL lamp can be commanded on for test purposes with the EST service tool by
                                requesting an Output State Check, if the OWL circuit checks out good to this point and
                                does not turn on when an Output State Check is commanded, either the ECM is bad or the
                                feature is not turned on.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Fault Code Description</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>263 = OWL Output Circuit Check Fault detected during a key on engine off standard
                                test, possible open or short in OWL circuit.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
